          It's always good to win while playing in 2nd gear. You look at the stats and it seems close but it was anything but, Basel were done after the 2nd goal. Their attacks only really came as a result of a mixture of our sloppiness in possession and sitting off the ball rather than playing possession for possession sake (like we should've). Ramsey was poor as was Iwobi, apart from his tap-in. All in all I'm happy but I really question Wenger's player management at times, it is not a coincidence we have the worst injury lists per year and he regularly. With Cazorla injured, we can ill afford one or both of Alexis and Oezil to be also and any opportunity to rest them should be taken. Bring on the draw where we will play either Bayern or Real Madrid. :-p
